HEADWORD: Grume
<hw>Grume</hw> <pr>(gr⟦udd⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>grume</ets>, cf. F. <ets>grumeau</ets> a little heap, clot of
blood, dim. fr. L. <ets>grumus</ets>.]</ety> <def>A thick, viscid fluid;
a clot, as of blood.</def> <rj><au>Quincy.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

